redlineSystemMib.name: redlineSystemMib
redlineSystemMib.description: This MIB module contains Redline extensions to the SNMPv2 MIB System Group.

redlineSystemSerialNumber.name: redlineSystemSerialNumber
redlineSystemSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the unit.

redlineSystemSystemReboot.name: redlineSystemSystemReboot
redlineSystemSystemReboot.description: Setting this variable to 2 causes a reboot of the system.

redlineSystemDHCPServerIpAddressType.name: redlineSystemDHCPServerIpAddressType
redlineSystemDHCPServerIpAddressType.description: The INET address type of Ip address of DHCP server. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemDHCPServerIpAddress.name: redlineSystemDHCPServerIpAddress
redlineSystemDHCPServerIpAddress.description: The INET address of DHCP server. Note: This object can not be set if usage of DHCP server is disabled. An attempt to set the address will fail and return 'resourceUnavailable' error

redlineSystemIpAddressType.name: redlineSystemIpAddressType
redlineSystemIpAddressType.description: The INET address type of Ip address of the system. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemIpAddress.name: redlineSystemIpAddress
redlineSystemIpAddress.description: The INET address of the system. Note: This object can not be set if usage of DHCP server is enabled. An attempt to set the address will fail and return 'resourceUnavailable' error

redlineSystemSubnetMaskAddressType.name: redlineSystemSubnetMaskAddressType
redlineSystemSubnetMaskAddressType.description: The INET address type of subnet mask of the system. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemSubnetMask.name: redlineSystemSubnetMask
redlineSystemSubnetMask.description: The Subnet Mask of the system. Note: This object can not be set if usage of DHCP server is enabled. An attempt to set the address will fail and return 'resourceUnavailable' error

redlineSystemDefGatewayAddressType.name: redlineSystemDefGatewayAddressType
redlineSystemDefGatewayAddressType.description: The INET address type of the default gateway. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemDefGatewayAddress.name: redlineSystemDefGatewayAddress
redlineSystemDefGatewayAddress.description: The INET address of the default gateway. Note: This object can not be set if usage of DHCP server is enabled. An attempt to set the address will fail and return 'resourceUnavailable' error

redlineSystemSyslogServerIpAddressType.name: redlineSystemSyslogServerIpAddressType
redlineSystemSyslogServerIpAddressType.description: The INET address type of Ip address of Syslog server. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemSyslogServerIpAddress.name: redlineSystemSyslogServerIpAddress
redlineSystemSyslogServerIpAddress.description: The INET address of Syslog server. Note: Entering '0.0.0.0' as an address will indicate to the system that Syslog capability is not to be used.

redlineSystemSwActiveVersion.name: redlineSystemSwActiveVersion
redlineSystemSwActiveVersion.description: The s/w version of the active (running) image.

redlineSystemSwAlternateVersion.name: redlineSystemSwAlternateVersion
redlineSystemSwAlternateVersion.description: The s/w version of the alternate (non-active) image.

redlineSystemSwActivateAlternate.name: redlineSystemSwActivateAlternate
redlineSystemSwActivateAlternate.description: Setting this to 2 triggers the switch-over to the alternate s/w image and reboot of the system. Before the switch-over a validation of the alternate image is performed and if it fails the 'inconsistentValue' error status is returned.

redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateTable.name: redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateTable
redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateTable.description: This table contains at most one entry representing a software synchronization process that is either currently in progress or one that was completed. When requested synchronization,the active s/w i image and the active configuration are copied to the alternate s/w image and configuration, respectively. A management station can create this entry if and only if either the table is empty or the only entry is for a synchronization that has already been completed. An attempt to create or write this entry when a synchronization is already in progress results in the 'resourceUnavailable' error status. The redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateStatus state object is used to control and monitor a s/w synchronization process. Setting it to the 'synchronizeAlternate' value starts a new synchronization if none is active at the time (otherwise an error status is returned).

redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateEntry.name: redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateEntry
redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateEntry.description: This entry contains information about a current or last software synchronization.

redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateIndex.name: redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateIndex
redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateIndex.description: The index of the software isynchronization table. The only value allowed is 1.

redlineSystemSwSyncAlternate.name: redlineSystemSwSyncAlternate
redlineSystemSwSyncAlternate.description: Setting it to 2 will synchronize the alternate s/w image and configuration database, i.e. the active s/w image and the active configuration are copied to the alternate s/w image and configuration, respectively.

redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateStatus.name: redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateStatus
redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateStatus.description: The status of the current or last software synchronization.

redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateTimeEnded.name: redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateTimeEnded
redlineSystemSwSyncAlternateTimeEnded.description: The date and time this software synchronization finished.

redlineSystemSwDownloadTable.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadTable
redlineSystemSwDownloadTable.description: This table contains at most one entry representing a software download process that is either currently in progress or one that was completed. A management station can create this entry if and only if either the table is empty or the only entry is for a download that has already been completed. An attempt to create or write this entry when a download is already in progress results in the 'resourceUnavailable' error status. The redlineSystemSwDownloadStatus state object is used to control and monitor a s/w download process. Setting it to the 'download' value starts a new download if none is active at the time (otherwise an error status is returned).

redlineSystemSwDownloadEntry.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadEntry
redlineSystemSwDownloadEntry.description: This entry contains information about a current or last software download.

redlineSystemSwDownloadIndex.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadIndex
redlineSystemSwDownloadIndex.description: The index of the software download table. The only value allowed is 1.

redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpAddressType.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpAddressType
redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpAddressType.description: The INET address type of the software upgrade FTP server. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpAddress.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpAddress
redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpAddress.description: The INET address of the FTP server.

redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpPassword.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpPassword
redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpPassword.description: The FTP user password. After this object is created it is not accessible.

redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpFile.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpFile
redlineSystemSwDownloadFtpFile.description: The full software image file path name as required by the FTP server.

redlineSystemSwDownloadStatus.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadStatus
redlineSystemSwDownloadStatus.description: The status of the current or last software download.

redlineSystemSwDownloadTimeEnded.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadTimeEnded
redlineSystemSwDownloadTimeEnded.description: The date and time this software download finished.

redlineSystemSwDownloadFailureReason.name: redlineSystemSwDownloadFailureReason
redlineSystemSwDownloadFailureReason.description: The short explanation of why software download failed. In a case of success this object will contain empty string.

redlineSystemConfigBackupTable.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupTable
redlineSystemConfigBackupTable.description: This table contains at most one entry representing a configuration backup process that is either currently in progress or one that was completed. A management station can create this entry if and only if either the table is empty or the only entry is for a backup that has already been completed. An attempt to create or write this entry when a backup is already in progress results in the 'resourceUnavailable' error status.

redlineSystemConfigBackupEntry.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupEntry
redlineSystemConfigBackupEntry.description: This entry contains information about a current or last configuration backup.

redlineSystemConfigBackupIndex.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupIndex
redlineSystemConfigBackupIndex.description: The index of the software download table. The only value allowed is 1.

redlineSystemConfigBackupConfigType.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupConfigType
redlineSystemConfigBackupConfigType.description: Specifies the type of configuration to be backup.

redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpAddressType.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpAddressType
redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpAddressType.description: The INET address type of the configuration backup FTP server. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpAddress.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpAddress
redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpAddress.description: The INET address of the FTP server.

redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpPassword.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpPassword
redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpPassword.description: The FTP user password. After this object is created it is not accessible.

redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpFile.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpFile
redlineSystemConfigBackupFtpFile.description: The full software image file path name as required by the FTP server.

redlineSystemConfigBackupStatus.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupStatus
redlineSystemConfigBackupStatus.description: The status of the current or last configuration backup.

redlineSystemConfigBackupFailureReason.name: redlineSystemConfigBackupFailureReason
redlineSystemConfigBackupFailureReason.description: The short explanation of why configuration backup failed. In a case of success this object will contain empty string.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreTable.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreTable
redlineSystemConfigRestoreTable.description: This table contains at most one entry representing a configuration restore process that is either currently in progress or one that was completed. A management station can create this entry if and only if either the table is empty or the only entry is for a restore that has already been completed. An attempt to create or write this entry when a restore is already in progress results in the 'resourceUnavailable' error status. After the process is finished with the status set to 'success', then (and only then) the system will be automatically rebooted in order for the newly restored parameters to become active.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreEntry.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreEntry
redlineSystemConfigRestoreEntry.description: This entry contains information about a current or last configuration restore.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreIndex.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreIndex
redlineSystemConfigRestoreIndex.description: The index of the software download table. The only value allowed is 1.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreConfigType.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreConfigType
redlineSystemConfigRestoreConfigType.description: Specifies the type of configuration to be restored.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpAddressType.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpAddressType
redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpAddressType.description: The INET address type of the configuration restore FTP server. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpAddress.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpAddress
redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpAddress.description: The INET address of the FTP server.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpPassword.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpPassword
redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpPassword.description: The FTP user password. After this object is created it is not accessible.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpFile.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpFile
redlineSystemConfigRestoreFtpFile.description: The full software image file path name as required by the FTP server.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreStatus.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreStatus
redlineSystemConfigRestoreStatus.description: The status of the current or last configuration restore.

redlineSystemConfigRestoreFailureReason.name: redlineSystemConfigRestoreFailureReason
redlineSystemConfigRestoreFailureReason.description: The short explanation of why configuration restore failed. In a case of success this object will contain empty string.

redlineSystemTrapReceiverTable.name: redlineSystemTrapReceiverTable
redlineSystemTrapReceiverTable.description: This table contains information about provisioned trap receivers i.e. the trap receivers that this agent will send notifications to. The entries of this table are indexed by their IP address and port values. The maximum number of entries in this table is eight.

redlineSystemTrapReceiverEntry.name: redlineSystemTrapReceiverEntry
redlineSystemTrapReceiverEntry.description: This entry contains information about a provisioned trap receiver (a trap destination from the agent's point of view.

redlineSystemTrapReceiverAddressType.name: redlineSystemTrapReceiverAddressType
redlineSystemTrapReceiverAddressType.description: The INET address type of the trap receiver.

redlineSystemTrapReceiverAddress.name: redlineSystemTrapReceiverAddress
redlineSystemTrapReceiverAddress.description: The INET address of the trap receiver.

redlineSystemTrapReceiverPort.name: redlineSystemTrapReceiverPort
redlineSystemTrapReceiverPort.description: The UDP port of the trap receiver.

redlineSystemTrapReceiverCommunity.name: redlineSystemTrapReceiverCommunity
redlineSystemTrapReceiverCommunity.description: The community string of the trap receiver.

redlineSystemTrapReceiverStatus.name: redlineSystemTrapReceiverStatus
redlineSystemTrapReceiverStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the redlineSystemTrapReceiverTable table. Only the 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' values can be specified in a set operation when an entry is created or destroyed, respectively.

redlineSystemTrapActivationTable.name: redlineSystemTrapActivationTable
redlineSystemTrapActivationTable.description: This table contains information about trap activation in the system i.e. the trap generation can be enabled or disabled. The entries of this table are indexed by the trap OID.

redlineSystemTrapActivationEntry.name: redlineSystemTrapActivationEntry
redlineSystemTrapActivationEntry.description: This entry contains information about trap acgtivation state.

redlineSystemTrapObjectID.name: redlineSystemTrapObjectID
redlineSystemTrapObjectID.description: Identifies the trap which generation is to be controlled by this entry.

redlineSystemTrapEnable.name: redlineSystemTrapEnable
redlineSystemTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether the system is permitted to generate traps specified by this entry.

redlineSystemPingTrapTrigger.name: redlineSystemPingTrapTrigger
redlineSystemPingTrapTrigger.description: Causes a ping trap to be sent

redlineSWUpgradeStatusTrap.name: redlineSWUpgradeStatusTrap
redlineSWUpgradeStatusTrap.description: Event that reports SW Upgrade progress and status changes.

redlineSystemAccessCtrlTable.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlTable
redlineSystemAccessCtrlTable.description: This table contains a list of hosts which are allowed to access the system. Each entry associated with the host, has ip address and read and write passwords. Only hosts identified by a right combination of ipAddress and password will be allowed to access the system. An entry can contain Ip address of '0.0.0.0'. In which case all hosts using password associated with this address will be granted access to the system. Initially, the table will contain only one entry with Ip address set to '0.0.0.0', read community set to 'public' and write community set to 'private'. The maximum number of entries in this table is eight

redlineSystemAccessCtrlEntry.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlEntry
redlineSystemAccessCtrlEntry.description: This entry contains privacy information about a host allowed to access the system.

redlineSystemAccessCtrlIndex.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlIndex
redlineSystemAccessCtrlIndex.description: The index of the Snmp Access Control table.

redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddrType.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddrType
redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddrType.description: The INET address type of the host allowed to access the system. IPv4 type supported only.

redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddr.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddr
redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddr.description: The INET address of the host allowed to access the system.

redlineSystemAccessCtrlReadCommunity.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlReadCommunity
redlineSystemAccessCtrlReadCommunity.description: The read community string associated with redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddress.

redlineSystemAccessCtrlWriteCommunity.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlWriteCommunity
redlineSystemAccessCtrlWriteCommunity.description: The write community string associated with redlineSystemAccessCtrlManagerIpAddress.

redlineSystemAccessCtrlStatus.name: redlineSystemAccessCtrlStatus
redlineSystemAccessCtrlStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the redlineSystemTrapReceiverTable table. Only the 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' values can be specified in a set operation when an entry is created or destroyed, respectively.

redlineSystemCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities that implement this MIB module.
